title: My Dog's Face contest Final 4: Rusty Roo Roo vs. King Louis, Nile vs. Ellie
text:
Note, 6:30 a.m.: The poll was mistakenly closed briefly; it is now open for voting until 11:59 p.m.
And then there were four ... in each category.
That's right, canine folks. Two vote-offs are left in the My Dog's Face contest. And if you aren't dreaming about dog faces at this point, well, at least I am.
Monday, Oct. 19, you voted between Small Dogs Bali and Tegan, and between Large Dogs Red and Roxybella. ( See the winners )
Today (Tuesday), Oct. 20, you'll have one day to vote between Small Dogs King Louis and Rusty Roo Roo and between Large Dogs Nile and Ellie.
And Wednesday, Oct. 21, at 5 a.m., is the one-day championship vote-off. The two dog face champs will be announced Thursday morning, Oct. 22.
The polls will close at 11:59 p.m. each day. One vote per dog fan, please.
Yes, there is a prize. Each top dog gets a custom portrait in acrylic of his or her beautiful canine face (painted and donated by Portland artist Minae Lee ) and a $100 gift certificate to the pet store of choice. Winning entries may be published in The Oregonian or on OregonLive.
See official contest rules here .
